column1: To his left the spectators were a mass of packed bodies and laughing faces ; to his right the procession trundled along , an exuberant juggernaut of color , noise , and smell : ox-drawn parade carts festooned with ribbons dyed in the god 's colors ; groups of Forceless monks on foot , beating drums and blowing kanshas , great trumpets that curved over the shoulder and made a sound like a mythic beast dying in agony ; drays bearing huge wood-and-gilt statues of rata in his four guises of World Creator , Primal Warrior , Eon Sleeper , and Risen Judge ; litters with smaller images of some of rata 's more powerful Aspects -- Ddarshi , Patron of luck , Skambys , Patron of war and weather , Hatspa , Patron of fire and weaponry , Tane , Patron of crops and the moon -- carried by hymn-singing devotee-priests .
